      "content": "While ibuprofen can provide relief, taking 400mg every 2 hours may lead to an increased risk of side effects such as stomach ulcers and bleeding. Nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) like ibuprofen can also interfere with kidney function if taken excessively. Consider taking ibuprofen as directed on the label, and consult a doctor or pharmacist for personalized advice on managing your lower back pain. They can also recommend alternative treatments or medications.",
